SIMPLE: epicurean
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Epicurean
<hw>Ep`i*cu*re"an</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Epicureus</ets>, Gr. <?/: cf. <ets>⟦eacute⟧picurien</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Pertaining to Epicurus, or following his
philosophy.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The sect <xex>Epicurean</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Given to luxury; adapted to luxurious tastes;
luxurious; pertaining to good eating.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Courses of the most refined and <qex>epicurean</qex> dishes.</q>
<rj><qau>Prescott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Epicurean philosophy</b></col>. <cd>See <cref>Atomic
philosophy</cref>, under <er>Atomic</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epicurean</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Epicurean
<hw>Ep`i*cu*re"an</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A follower or
Epicurus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One given to epicurean indulgence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epicureanism</ent>⟦br⟧
